5 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
6 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
7 Article – Health – General
8 21–101.
9 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
10 (i) “Food” means:
11 (1) Any substance that is used as food or drink for human beings or as a
12 component of food or drink for human beings; or
13 (2) Chewing gum or any substance that is used as a component of chewing
14 gum.
15 21–259.4.
16 A PERSON MAY NOT SELL FOOD THAT CONTAINS RED DYE NO. 3 (CAS NO.
17 16423–68–0) IN THE STATE UNLESS THE FOOD PACKAGING INCLUDES A
18 CONSPICUOUS WARNING LABEL THAT STATES THE FOOD CONTAINS RED DYE NO. 3.
19 21–1215.
20 (a) This section does not apply to a violation of § 21–220(b)(4), § 21–228, or §
21 21–259.3 of this title.
22 (b) A person who violates any provision of Subtitle 2 of this title or any regulation
23 adopted under Subtitle 2 of this title is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction is subject
24 to:
25 (1) A fine not exceeding $10,000 or imprisonment not exceeding 1 year or
26 both; or
27 (2) If the person has been convicted once of violating Subtitle 2 of this title,
28 a fine not exceeding $25,000 or imprisonment not exceeding 3 years or both.
29 (c) In addition to any criminal penalties imposed under this section, a person who
30 violates any provision of Subtitle 2 of this title, any rule or regulation adopted under
31 Subtitle 2 of this title, or any term, condition, or limitation of any license or registration
32 issued under Subtitle 2 of this title:

